{{Expand German|MARTa|date=August 2012}} {{Infobox museum | name = MARTa Herford | native_name = | native_name_lang = | image = Herford MARTa 88.jpg | imagesize = 270 | caption = As seen from Goebenstrasse, a few days before opening | alt = | map_type = | map_caption = | map_alt = | established = 2005 | dissolved = | coordinates = {{coord|52.120982|8.668325|display=inline}} | location = [[Herford]], [[North Rhine-Westphalia]], [[Germany]] | type =Station | network = | website = http://marta-herford.de/?lang=en }}
'''MARTa Herford''' is a contemporary art museum in [[Herford]], [[Germany]].
== Building and history ==
The idea for the museum formed in 2000, drawing from Herford's status as a German center of furniture and home furnishing production.<ref name="marta-herford1">{{cite web|url=http://marta-herford.de/index.php/4619-2/?lang=en |title=MARTa Herford: Idea & Concept |publisher=Marta-herford.de |date=2005-05-07 |accessdate=2013-09-13}}</ref> The name ''MARTa'' is an acronym for ''Möbel'' ([[German language|German]] for ''furniture''), ''ART'' (simply ''art'' in English), and ''Ambiente'' (ambience).<ref name="mff">{{cite book |title=Frank Gehry MARTa Herford |year=2005 |publisher=Birkhäuser |location=Basel |isbn=978-3764371623 |<!-- accessdate=August 12, 2012 -->}}</ref> The founding director of the museum was [[Jan Hoet]], a noted Belgian curator. {{Interlanguage link multi|Roland Nachtigäller|de}} took over as director in 2009.
The building was designed by [[Frank Gehry]] and built by [[Archimedes GmbH]].<ref>{{cite web|author=MARTa Freunde und Förderer (Editor) |url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/3764371625 |title=Frank Gehry MARTa Herford (German and English Edition): MARTa Freunde und Förderer: 9783764371623: Amazon.com: Books |publisher=Amazon.com |date=2005-05-06 |accessdate=2013-09-13}}</ref> Construction began in 2001,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.arcspace.com/architects/gehry/herford/index.html |accessdate=August 12, 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120315164222/http://www.arcspace.com/architects/gehry/herford/index.html |archivedate=March 15, 2012 }}</ref> and it officially opened to the public on May 7, 2005.<ref name="marta-herford1"/>
