{{Unreferenced|date=July 2014}} {{Infobox park | name = Museumpark | photo = Museumpark Rotterdam.jpg | photo_width = 250px | photo_caption = Museumpark with [[Museum Boijmans Van Beuningen]] in the background in 2007 | map = | map_width = | type = [[Urban park]] | location = [[Rotterdam Centrum]] | nearest_city = | coords = | area = | created = 1927 | operator = | visitation_num = | status = | designation = | open = }}
'''Museumpark''' is an [[urban park]] in [[Rotterdam]], [[Netherlands]], located between the [[Museum Boijmans Van Beuningen]], [[Westersingel]], [[Westzeedijk]] and the complex of the [[Erasmus MC]], a medical centre affiliated with the [[Erasmus University]].
The park lies on the former land of the Hoboken family, who lived in the building that is now the [[Natuurhistorisch Museum Rotterdam]]. The park was laid out in 1927 to the design of the architect Witteveen. On the south side of the pond in the park a monument for Gerrit Jongh, director of municipal works in Rotterdam. There are several [[work of art|artwork]]s in the park, so it also serves as a [[sculpture garden]].
There are a number of museums located in the vicinity of the park, hence the name:
* The [[Netherlands Architecture Institute]] (NAi) * [[Museum Boijmans Van Beuningen]] * The [[Chabot Museum]] * The [[Kunsthal]] * [[Villa Sonneveld]] * [[Natuurhistorisch Museum Rotterdam]]
